00:22:36,856 --> 00:22:38,774
Huh.
It's terrifying,

530
00:22:38,816 --> 00:22:41,777
and it's exhilarating.

531
00:22:41,819 --> 00:22:43,654
[Sighs]

532
00:22:43,696 --> 00:22:45,072
Well...

533
00:22:45,114 --> 00:22:48,784
I have been known
to change my mind, though.

534
00:22:48,826 --> 00:22:51,245
Yeah.

535
00:22:51,287 --> 00:22:52,538
Microsoft's safe.

536
00:22:52,579 --> 00:22:54,748
But, um,
well, what's that saying?

537
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:57,543
No risk, no reward, right?

538
00:22:57,584 --> 00:22:58,836
I'm in.

539
00:22:58,878 --> 00:23:01,797
If you still want me,
that is.

540
00:23:01,839 --> 00:23:03,799
I-I -- Y-- Absolutely!

541
00:23:03,841 --> 00:23:05,218
Okay, okay.
[Laughs]

542
00:23:05,259 --> 00:23:07,011
[Gasps]

543
00:23:07,053 --> 00:23:09,513
I might need your shark side
to help me out, though.

544
00:23:09,555 --> 00:23:11,807
The Beast of Redmond
ain't gonna like this one bit.
Oh.

545
00:23:11,849 --> 00:23:13,559
They don't scare me.

546
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:15,102
Yeah,
I can't imagine who would.

547
00:23:15,144 --> 00:23:16,979
[Chuckles]

548
00:23:17,021 --> 00:23:17,980
To risk.

549
00:23:18,022 --> 00:23:21,359
[Sighs, chuckles]

550
00:23:21,399 --> 00:23:23,194
♪♪

551
00:23:23,236 --> 00:23:26,572
Ahh!

552
00:23:26,613 --> 00:23:28,657
Hey.
You up for one more?

553
00:23:37,333 --> 00:23:39,877
[Dog barking in distance]

554
00:23:43,756 --> 00:23:46,133
[Sighs]

555
00:23:56,434 --> 00:23:59,105
[Groans, clears throat]

556
00:23:59,146 --> 00:24:01,648
Ah.

557
00:24:07,363 --> 00:24:08,406
Hey.

558
00:24:08,446 --> 00:24:10,366
Hello.
[Clears throat]

559
00:24:10,408 --> 00:24:11,784
Feeling okay...?

560
00:24:11,825 --> 00:24:13,786
Yeah.

561
00:24:13,827 --> 00:24:16,538
Uh, there's coffee...

562
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:20,751
I should, uh --
I should get going.

563
00:24:23,087 --> 00:24:26,048
Yeah, we should, um...

564
00:24:26,090 --> 00:24:27,716
We should talk
about the job --

565
00:24:27,758 --> 00:24:29,551
You know...

566
00:24:29,593 --> 00:24:33,680
it's fine.

567
00:24:33,722 --> 00:24:34,514
Yeah.

568
00:24:34,556 --> 00:24:36,183
O-Okay.

569
00:24:38,769 --> 00:24:40,771
[Sighs]

570
00:24:40,813 --> 00:24:43,690
["Jump Right Out
of This Jukebox" plays]

571
00:24:43,732 --> 00:24:47,445
♪♪

572
00:24:47,485 --> 00:24:49,405
♪ Suppose that
I should come to life ♪

573
00:24:49,447 --> 00:24:50,739
[Knock on door]
John?

574
00:24:50,781 --> 00:24:52,825
♪ When they play this song ♪

575
00:24:52,866 --> 00:24:55,244
♪ I could be in a lot of places
at once ♪

576
00:24:55,286 --> 00:24:56,870
It's from Sam.

577
00:24:56,912 --> 00:24:59,248
Oh.

578
00:24:59,290 --> 00:25:02,084
[Chuckles]

579
00:25:02,126 --> 00:25:03,336
Aww.

580
00:25:03,377 --> 00:25:04,920
That's me with all the hair.

581
00:25:04,962 --> 00:25:07,465
[Both laugh]

582
00:25:07,505 --> 00:25:09,549
♪♪

583
00:25:09,591 --> 00:25:12,261
What a kid.

584
00:25:12,303 --> 00:25:14,763
John,
this whole experience...

585
00:25:14,805 --> 00:25:18,142
it's been making me think.

586
00:25:18,184 --> 00:25:20,478
At the hospital,
it was so hard.

587
00:25:20,518 --> 00:25:22,188
I had no say
in your care

588
00:25:22,229 --> 00:25:23,397
and if something
had gone wrong...

589
00:25:23,439 --> 00:25:25,149
Yeah, but it didn't.

590
00:25:25,191 --> 00:25:27,318
I'm fine...

591
00:25:27,360 --> 00:25:28,986
Well, it's not just that.

592
00:25:29,028 --> 00:25:31,155
[Sighs]

593
00:25:31,197 --> 00:25:34,908
At the restaurant,
there was a moment...

594
00:25:34,950 --> 00:25:38,078
the way you looked.

595
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:39,497
I thought
I was losing you.

596
00:25:39,537 --> 00:25:42,208
Oh.

597
00:25:42,249 --> 00:25:44,168
I love you.

598
00:25:44,210 --> 00:25:48,297
And I don't know how much time
together we have left.

599
00:25:48,339 --> 00:25:51,884
So what're we waiting for?

600
00:25:51,925 --> 00:25:54,845
Now, I don't have a ring --

601
00:25:54,887 --> 00:25:56,972
And I know
you're expecting a big rock...

602
00:25:57,014 --> 00:26:01,477
Goddamn, woman,
what're you doing to my heart?

603
00:26:01,519 --> 00:26:03,187
So...?

604
00:26:03,229 --> 00:26:08,317
♪♪

605
00:26:08,359 --> 00:26:12,946
Do you remember the
Patterson housing development?

606
00:26:12,988 --> 00:26:15,199
You passed on it.

607
00:26:15,241 --> 00:26:17,368
I thought
it was worth a second look.

608
00:26:17,410 --> 00:26:20,829
♪♪

609
00:26:20,871 --> 00:26:22,122
How much?

610
00:26:22,164 --> 00:26:23,957
300k.

611
00:26:23,999 --> 00:26:26,668
I wanted to take care of it
myself.

612
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:30,130
I didn't want you to know
what a fool I was --

613
00:26:30,172 --> 00:26:32,341
I thought workin' at Rover
would be a win-win,

614
00:26:32,383 --> 00:26:37,595
and then we started hitting
a wall, and I panicked.

615
00:26:37,637 --> 00:26:41,183
You saw the site.
It wasn't good enough.

616
00:26:41,225 --> 00:26:43,643
We couldn't get over
that hump.

617
00:26:43,685 --> 00:26:49,066
So I-I got Cam to help build
the search engine.

618
00:26:49,108 --> 00:26:51,068
And Donna found out,

619
00:26:51,110 --> 00:26:53,779
and then at restaurant,
she knew that she --

620
00:26:53,820 --> 00:26:56,490
I'm sorry.

621
00:26:56,532 --> 00:26:57,908
Diane.

622
00:26:57,950 --> 00:26:59,952
♪♪

623
00:26:59,993 --> 00:27:02,704
Diane!

624
00:27:02,746 --> 00:27:06,125
[Indistinct conversations]

625
00:27:06,166 --> 00:27:07,501
♪♪

626
00:27:07,543 --> 00:27:12,172
[Breathes deeply]

627
00:27:12,214 --> 00:27:14,800
♪♪

628
00:27:14,841 --> 00:27:18,845
Haley? C'mere.

629
00:27:23,309 --> 00:27:27,271
What is it? Pete's waiting
to take me back to school.

630
00:27:27,313 --> 00:27:30,941
We need to talk
about your grades.

631
00:27:30,983 --> 00:27:33,902
Okay...

632
00:27:33,944 --> 00:27:35,613
The school called.

633
00:27:35,653 --> 00:27:38,115
They said that
you're failing two classes.
Failing?

634
00:27:38,157 --> 00:27:41,327
I -- Maybe I missed a few tests,
but I can just retake them.

635
00:27:41,368 --> 00:27:42,328
Well...
I'll talk to my teacher.
I can...

636
00:27:42,369 --> 00:27:45,205
We agreed
that you could work here

637
00:27:45,247 --> 00:27:47,166
<i>if</i> you kept up your grades.

638
00:27:47,207 --> 00:27:49,376
That was the deal.

639
00:27:49,418 --> 00:27:51,878
S-So what're you saying?
I have to stop working?

640
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:54,173
Just temporarily until you can
bring your grades back up,

641
00:27:54,214 --> 00:27:55,549
and then we can talk --

642
00:27:55,591 --> 00:27:57,259
But, Dad --
It's<i> Haley's</i> Comet!

643
00:27:57,301 --> 00:27:59,178
You wouldn't even have
a company if weren't for me!

644
00:27:59,219 --> 00:28:00,762
Hey, listen.
Calm down, Bug.

645
00:28:00,804 --> 00:28:02,848
That's not entirely accurate.
Stop calling me "Bug"!

646
00:28:02,889 --> 00:28:04,141
And why do
I even need school?

647
00:28:04,183 --> 00:28:05,434
I already have a job.

648
00:28:05,476 --> 00:28:07,561
Because you need school
to learn

649
00:28:07,603 --> 00:28:09,855
and to make friends --
My friends are here --

650
00:28:09,896 --> 00:28:12,650
And you can't fire me,
they need me!

651
00:28:12,690 --> 00:28:15,653
[Chuckling] Okay, well, I think
we'd be able to manage --

652
00:28:15,693 --> 00:28:18,447
Hey!

653
00:28:18,489 --> 00:28:22,493
Haley, clean it up.

654
00:28:22,535 --> 00:28:25,454
No.
Haley, if you ever want
to work here again,

655
00:28:25,496 --> 00:28:27,373
you will clean. It. Up.

656
00:28:28,748 --> 00:28:30,459
Haley!
[Door opens]

657
00:28:33,295 --> 00:28:36,131
[Indistinct conversations]
Ha-- Hey!

658
00:28:36,173 --> 00:28:38,258
Get back here!

659
00:28:38,300 --> 00:28:41,428
Haley!

660
00:28:41,470 --> 00:28:43,472
[Conversations stop]

661
00:28:43,514 --> 00:28:44,931
[Door closes]
What?!

662
00:28:44,973 --> 00:28:47,059
[Conversations resume]

663
00:28:52,772 --> 00:28:54,441
[Sighs]

664
00:28:54,483 --> 00:28:58,820
[Breathes deeply]

665
00:28:58,862 --> 00:29:00,406
Yes,
it's a red leather wallet.

666
00:29:00,447 --> 00:29:02,658
I was siting at the bar...

667
00:29:02,700 --> 00:29:03,783
You do?

668
00:29:03,825 --> 00:29:05,369
[Knock on door]

669
00:29:05,411 --> 00:29:08,038
I-I will come by tonight.
Thank you.

670
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:10,165
[Telephone clicks in cradle,
door closes]

671
00:29:10,207 --> 00:29:11,458
Do you have a moment?

672
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:13,001
What's going on...?

673
00:29:13,043 --> 00:29:16,338
[Sighs]

674
00:29:16,380 --> 00:29:18,257
I had a talk with John.

675
00:29:18,298 --> 00:29:21,801
And apparently
he's made some bad decisions

676
00:29:21,843 --> 00:29:23,095
regarding Rover.

677
00:29:23,136 --> 00:29:25,723
But I think
you already know that.

678
00:29:25,764 --> 00:29:28,559
Well, I [Sighs]

679
00:29:28,601 --> 00:29:30,102
I had my suspicions,

680
00:29:30,143 --> 00:29:33,647
but I didn't know for sure
until I saw Cam...

681
00:29:33,689 --> 00:29:35,566
It's done.

682
00:29:35,608 --> 00:29:36,858
Now, the important thing

683
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:39,152
is to clean up the mess
and move on.

684
00:29:39,194 --> 00:29:42,155
I couldn't agree more.
Cecil is gone.

685
00:29:42,197 --> 00:29:43,490
We plan to find someone

686
00:29:43,532 --> 00:29:44,824
who can reverse engineer
Rover's code --

687
00:29:44,866 --> 00:29:46,243
Reverse engineer?
Why?

688
00:29:46,285 --> 00:29:48,287
Oh, to protect the site
from any liabilities --

689
00:29:48,328 --> 00:29:50,623
But if Cameron
built this code,

690
00:29:50,664 --> 00:29:52,249
the next step --
the<i> only</i> step --

691
00:29:52,291 --> 00:29:53,751
is to get her
to sign a release.

692
00:29:53,792 --> 00:29:54,918
That's how we protect
the site.

693
00:29:54,960 --> 00:29:57,421
Yes, yes.
[Sighs]

694
00:29:57,463 --> 00:29:59,423
But in this one case,

695
00:29:59,465 --> 00:30:02,342
I really think
that is the wrong move.

696
00:30:02,384 --> 00:30:04,219
I mean, why let Cameron know

697
00:30:04,261 --> 00:30:06,179
how valuable
what she gave us was?

698
00:30:06,221 --> 00:30:07,973
I mean, better
to just create our own version

699
00:30:08,014 --> 00:30:09,975
of the algorithm,
and no one will be any wiser.

700
00:30:10,016 --> 00:30:11,977
That doesn't make any sense.

701
00:30:12,018 --> 00:30:13,270
Look, there is
one simple solution,

702
00:30:13,312 --> 00:30:14,813
and it should've happened
immediately:

703
00:30:14,854 --> 00:30:16,690
pay Cameron whatever she wants
and be done with it.

704
00:30:16,732 --> 00:30:18,817
No!
I can't. I can't.

705
00:30:18,858 --> 00:30:21,027
I-I just...

706
00:30:21,069 --> 00:30:22,988
I-I can't.

707
00:30:23,029 --> 00:30:26,617
[Sighs]

708
00:30:34,958 --> 00:30:37,294
Well, this is
what's gonna happen.

709
00:30:37,336 --> 00:30:38,754
You're going
to go to Cameron

710
00:30:38,796 --> 00:30:40,464
and get her
to sign a release.

711
00:30:40,506 --> 00:30:42,675
And then
you will step away.

712
00:30:42,716 --> 00:30:44,843
And Trip will take over.

713
00:30:44,884 --> 00:30:47,763
Th-- I...

714
00:30:47,805 --> 00:30:49,723
That's not fair.

715
00:30:49,765 --> 00:30:51,391
He'll just --
He'll -- You know him.

716
00:30:51,433 --> 00:30:53,310
He'll use it!
To become managing partner?

717
00:30:53,352 --> 00:30:54,353
Perhaps.

718
00:30:54,394 --> 00:30:55,937
Maybe that's best.

719
00:30:55,979 --> 00:30:58,524
Frankly, you have
bigger issues to deal with.

720
00:30:58,565 --> 00:30:59,775
Get yourself together,
Donna.

721
00:30:59,817 --> 00:31:01,026
I'm tired
of holding your hand.

722
00:31:01,067 --> 00:31:02,361
None of this
would've happened

723
00:31:02,402 --> 00:31:05,030
if Bos felt like he could
just come and talk to you.

724
00:31:12,412 --> 00:31:15,582
[Door opens]
[Breathes sharply]

725
00:31:15,624 --> 00:31:17,543
[Door closes]

726
00:31:20,295 --> 00:31:22,922
[Sighs]

727
00:31:22,964 --> 00:31:24,299
I was surprised
to get your e-mail.

728
00:31:24,341 --> 00:31:26,593
I was about
to give up on you.

729
00:31:26,635 --> 00:31:28,846
Yeah. Um...

730
00:31:28,887 --> 00:31:31,473
So what is this about,
exactly?

731
00:31:31,515 --> 00:31:32,850
You, um...

732
00:31:32,891 --> 00:31:34,810
Did Atari send you or --
Oh, no.

733
00:31:34,852 --> 00:31:36,144
Although
they were kind enough

734
00:31:36,186 --> 00:31:37,855
to give me
a copy of "Pilgrim."

735
00:31:37,896 --> 00:31:41,149
They did?
You can get anything
if you know how to ask.

736
00:31:41,191 --> 00:31:43,068
I thought the game
was interesting --

737
00:31:43,109 --> 00:31:45,404
flawed, but interesting.

738
00:31:45,445 --> 00:31:46,488
I mean,
I've never played a game

739
00:31:46,530 --> 00:31:49,324
that actively blocks
your way so much.

740
00:31:49,366 --> 00:31:51,284
Yeah.

741
00:31:51,326 --> 00:31:56,915
Well, I, uh -- I was trying
to respect the gamer.

742
00:31:56,956 --> 00:31:58,584
Engage them,

743
00:31:58,625 --> 00:32:00,586
not treat them like
a passive receptacle, but --
Respect, sure,

744
00:32:00,627 --> 00:32:03,505
but you clearly didn't want
anyone to solve the game.

745
00:32:03,547 --> 00:32:05,883
Why, I have no idea.
That's your thing.

746
00:32:05,924 --> 00:32:10,262
But the world that you created
to contain the puzzles,

747
00:32:10,303 --> 00:32:12,681
<i>that</i> was interesting.

748
00:32:12,723 --> 00:32:16,602
And the graphics
were incredible.

749
00:32:16,643 --> 00:32:18,228
I'm sure they still
don't even come close

750
00:32:18,270 --> 00:32:19,688
to what you saw
in your head.

751
00:32:19,730 --> 00:32:21,356
Well, the computer for that
doesn't exist yet.

752
00:32:21,398 --> 00:32:22,982
You sure?

753
00:32:23,024 --> 00:32:25,318
Processor speed is growing
at an exponential rate.

754
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:27,654
I've seen what's happening,
and it's mind-blowing.

755
00:32:27,696 --> 00:32:29,197
'Cause here's the thing:

756
00:32:29,239 --> 00:32:31,909
I don't think
you're a game designer.
Oh.

757
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:34,077
I think
you're a world builder.

758
00:32:34,119 --> 00:32:36,329
♪♪

759
00:32:36,371 --> 00:32:39,416
And I'd like
to work with you.

760
00:32:39,458 --> 00:32:41,919
I want to see
what you do next.

761
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:44,797
♪ You're gonna wake up ♪

762
00:32:44,838 --> 00:32:47,382
Okay.

763
00:32:47,424 --> 00:32:49,676
And why should
I want to work with you?

764
00:32:49,718 --> 00:32:51,094
Because here's
what I'm offering:

765
00:32:51,136 --> 00:32:55,181
no VCs.
No interference.

766
00:32:55,223 --> 00:32:57,142
What you said at MISC
was spot on:

767
00:32:57,183 --> 00:32:58,727
The model is broken.

768
00:32:58,769 --> 00:33:00,145
Parasitic.

769
00:33:00,186 --> 00:33:02,815
So I plan
to stay out of your way.

770
00:33:02,856 --> 00:33:05,901
While I do what, exactly?

771
00:33:05,943 --> 00:33:08,695
Whatever you want.

772
00:33:08,737 --> 00:33:11,114
♪♪

773
00:33:11,156 --> 00:33:13,199
[Indistinct conversations]

774
00:33:13,241 --> 00:33:15,869
You okay?

775
00:33:15,911 --> 00:33:17,537
Yup.

776
00:33:17,579 --> 00:33:19,581
You wanna talk?
Nope.

777
00:33:19,623 --> 00:33:22,208
Hound Dogz.

778
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:24,962
We were just there
yesterday.

779
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:26,880
Yep.
She loves that place.

780
00:33:26,922 --> 00:33:29,758
No idea why,
the food sucks.

781
00:33:29,800 --> 00:33:31,844
Maybe it's not about
the food.

782
00:33:31,885 --> 00:33:35,639
[Sighs]

783
00:33:35,681 --> 00:33:37,808
When's she coming back?

784
00:33:37,850 --> 00:33:41,144
No idea.
She no longer works here.

785
00:33:41,186 --> 00:33:43,146
What did you do,
fire her?

786
00:33:43,188 --> 00:33:46,024
I gave her a choice,
and she walked.

787
00:33:46,065 --> 00:33:48,026
So get her back.

788
00:33:48,067 --> 00:33:49,736
Joe, she's flunking
her classes

789
00:33:49,778 --> 00:33:51,905
and copping
some major attitude.

790
00:33:51,947 --> 00:33:55,200
You don't understand,
Haley needs this place.

791
00:33:55,241 --> 00:33:57,828
She's not like other kids.

792
00:33:57,870 --> 00:34:01,414
She's got different, um...

793
00:34:01,456 --> 00:34:02,749
interests.

794
00:34:02,791 --> 00:34:05,836
